{"key":"processedPost-9431482","value":{"id":9431482,"first":9429286,"last":9439075,"when":1229299390,"utime":"12/15/08 02:03 AM","content":"Mist the substrate trays and/or cakes, whether they're cased or not, and the perlite.&nbsp; Of course some is going to get on the walls of the FC and it helps.&nbsp; However, the perlite has a million or more times the surface area of the walls, so that's where you want your moisture going so it can do some good.&nbsp; <br /><br />My point is that to mist the walls <i>only</i> per the advice of hundreds of posts here that parrot previous bad advice is flat out wrong.&nbsp; If you're giving proper air exchange, your substrate <i>will</i> dry out, even if you have 99% humidity.&nbsp; Therefore, you need to mist to make up for the lost moisture.&nbsp; This wetting, and then drying between mist cycles is a major pinning trigger.<br />RR","title":"Re: caps folding up? and some FC questions... (pics)"}}